OL,7,FThey added: "In our view, he should
OL,8,Fnot be allowed any privileges
OL,9,Fwhatsoever while serving a sentence
OL,10,Ffor the deaths of 22 innocent lives
OL,11,Fand the injuring of many more.
OL,13,F"He should not have access to anything
OL,14,Fthat he can weaponise, such as hot oil
OL,15,For items he can turn into blades."
OL,17,FSpeaking to Good Morning Britain, the
OL,18,Fmum of another victim, Olivia Campbell-
OL,19,FHardy, who was killed aged 15, said
